Ρ. 25, 1. 1. octingenti fere] From the year of the city 245 to the year of this speech 700 there are 455 years. Had there always been consuls, there would have been 910 of them in this period, not including the consules suffecti. But the number is diminished by one year in which the decemviri hindered the electiori of consuls, by fifty years in which tribuni militum consulari potestate were in power, by five years in which there were solitudines magistratuum, and by three years in which a Dictator and a magister equitum without consuls held the supreme power (A.U.C. 430, 445, 453). Accordingly we must make a deductiori of at least 118 consuls for these fifty-nine years; there remain then 79² (octingenti sere), among whom there were certainly more chosen‚ while others again were replaced by suffecti.
